Simple Driver
=============


1/ make the device
     the driver makes the device nodes for you
     my_driver_01.c

2/ basic open/close/read/write
     my_driver_02.c

3/ add proc
     my_driver_03.c

4/ add ioctl
     my_driver_04.c

5/ add mmap
     my_driver_05.c



Run this with

   sudo insmod ./my_driver_xx.ko

to add the module to the kernel
and

   sudo rmmod ./my_driver_xx.ko
to remove the module from the kernel

The printk output placed in /var/log/messages
You can use the "dmesg" command to look at this output

dmesg
[...]
